Class BrailleCell

  • java.lang.Object
    • enamel.BrailleCell

  • public class BrailleCell
extends java.lang.Object
    This class implements a Braille Cell with 8 pins. The class contains methods for displaying letters on the cell as well as raising and/or lowering individual pins. The pins are boolean objects stored in a boolean array field called listOfPins. boolean allows abstracting the pins, which by definition can only have two states. This allows for graphical, auditory, and other implementations (i.e. hardware braille cell, Metec B11) to show the braille cell to the user in different forms.

    This class supports the standard Braille encoding of English characters plus the space character using the displayCharacter() method. For any non-standard characters or ones that aren't included by default, use the setPins() method, which takes a string of 1s and 0s as argument and sets the pins accordingly. 1 meaning raised and 0 meaning lowered. The constructor of this class is not public. Objects are created when a Simulator object is created. Use the getCell method of class Simulator to obtain references to individual BrailleCell objects.

    Author:
    Team 4: Yassin Mohamed, Qassim Allauddin, Derek Li, Artem Solovey., ENAMEL team: Sunjik Lee, Li Yin, Vassilios Tzerpos.

    • Method Detail

      • displayCharacter

        public void displayCharacter(char a)
                      throws java.lang.InterruptedException
        Displays the character passed as argument on this Braille Cell object in Braille.

        The method works by selecting specific booleans in listOfPins that represent raised "pins", or the parts of the letter that would be felt by a human hand, and setting it to true, while setting the "pins" that are not raised to false.

        Parameters:
        a - the char letter to display.
        Throws:
        java.lang.InterruptedException - if the argument is not within our alphabet of English letters.

      • setPins

        public void setPins(java.lang.String pins)
        Takes an eight character string of 1s and 0s as argument, and sets the the 8 pins accordingly. 1 corresponds to raising the pin, 0 to lowering it. The first 3 characters correspond to the top-left pin to the third from the top pin on the left side. The second 3 characters correspond to the top-right pin to the third from the top pin on the right side. The last 2 characters correspond to the bottom-left and the bottom-right pins. This arrangement is to support to the Metec B11 Braille Cell's arrangement of the pins, which is arranged the same.
        Parameters:
        pins - string of 1s and 0s that is 8 characters long that sets the state of the eight pins that form the cell
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the string is not 8 characters long or if it contains any character that isn't a 1 or a 0
